The paper discusses the impact of soft errors in uncore components of a System-on-a-Chip (SoC), which involves the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.AR (Architecture), as the paper focuses on the design and behavior of the SoC architecture. The second likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper deals with multi-core SoCs and their system-level behaviors. The third likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering), as the paper discusses recovery techniques for soft errors in uncore components. The fourth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper analyzes the impact of soft errors on system-level reliability. The fifth likely category is cs.ET (Embedded Systems), as the paper deals with the design and behavior of a complex embedded system.
